If a quorum is not present, the meeting shall be recessed to the same day of the following week. If a quorum is not present at the second Town Meeting on the budget, the budget shall automatically be put to a referendum on the first Tuesday following the next Monday. If a majority of those voting at the referendum shall vote “yes,” then the budget shall stand approved. If a majority of those voting at the referendum shall vote “no,” then the proposed budget is defeated, and it shall be bifurcated as set forth below in <<Section 803D>>; and returned to the Board of Finance which shall review the rejected budget and shall present the same or a revised budget to a Town Meeting to be held on the next succeeding Tuesday.